          <section id="how" style="margin-top:14px">
            <h2>How it works — step by step</h2>
            <ol class="small">
              <li><strong>Choose the right service:</strong> compare fees, currency support, limits, speed, and integrations.</li>
              <li><strong>Verify your business:</strong> set up business accounts, complete KYC to lift limits and improve trust.</li>
              <li><strong>Integrate with your stack:</strong> connect gateways to ecommerce, invoicing, or accounting tools (APIs, plugins).</li>
              <li><strong>Set pricing & fees:</strong> decide who covers transfer fees and add currency conversion buffers if needed.</li>
              <li><strong>Automate payouts:</strong> schedule mass payouts to contractors or suppliers using batch tools or APIs.</li>
            </ol>
          </section>

          <section id="compare" class="card" style="margin-top:12px;padding:14px">
            <h2>Compare popular options (quick view)</h2>
            <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:10px">
              <div class="feature">
                <h3>PayPal / PayPal Business</h3>
                <div class="small">Great for buyer protection and global reach. Fees can be higher; good for marketplaces and quick buyer checkout.</div>
                <ul class="small">
                  <li>Strengths: ubiquity, buyer trust, easy checkout</li>
                  <li>Consider: conversion & withdrawal fees, disputes</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="feature">
                <h3>Wise (formerly TransferWise)</h3>
                <div class="small">Low-cost FX, transparent fees, multi-currency accounts — excellent for cross-border transfers and paying contractors.</div>
                <ul class="small">
                  <li>Strengths: low FX margin, multi-currency balances</li>
                  <li>Consider: not a checkout gateway — combine with payment processors</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="feature">
                <h3>Stripe</h3>
                <div class="small">Powerful payments platform with global payout options, subscriptions, and developer-friendly APIs.</div>
                <ul class="small">
                  <li>Strengths: subscriptions, fraud tools, extensible</li>
                  <li>Consider: setup complexity and country availability</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="feature">
                <h3>Revolut for Business</h3>
                <div class="small">Multi-currency accounts with cards and fast transfers — good for SMEs and teams working internationally.</div>
                <ul class="small">
                  <li>Strengths: corporate cards, FX limits</li>
                  <li>Consider: monthly plans may be needed for full features</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="feature">
                <h3>Local Wallets & Bank Transfers</h3>
                <div class="small">Local payment rails (e.g., UPI, Pix, SEPA) are usually cheapest and fastest within region — ideal for local customers.</div>
                <ul class="small">
                  <li>Strengths: low fees, high local adoption</li>
                  <li>Consider: integration and reconciliation complexity</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="feature">
                <h3>Escrow & Marketplaces</h3>
                <div class="small">Use escrow services or marketplace platforms when trust and dispute resolution are essential for higher-value transactions.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section style="margin-top:14px">
            <h2>Security & Compliance (must-do's)</h2>
            <ul class="small">
              <li>Enable 2-factor authentication on all business accounts.</li>
              <li>Complete KYC/AML checks and keep business documents up to date.</li>
              <li>Record and reconcile transfers weekly to catch errors quickly.</li>
              <li>Use invoice templates and clear payment terms (currency, who pays fees, refund policy).</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section style="margin-top:14px">
            <h2>Practical setups for common business models</h2>
            <div class="kpi" style="margin-top:10px">
              <div class="item">
                <strong>Ecommerce store:</strong> Stripe or PayPal for checkout + Wise for settling foreign earnings to your bank.
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <strong>Freelancers / Agencies:</strong> Wise or Revolut for fast contractor payouts; PayPal for client invoices.
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <strong>Marketplaces:</strong> Stripe Connect or PayPal Commerce Platform to split payments and handle KYC.
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="faq" class="card" style="margin-top:14px;padding:14px">
            <h2>FAQ — Related search queries</h2>
            <div class="faq small">
              <div class="q">Q: Which app is cheapest to send money internationally?</div>
              <div>A: Usually Wise for pure currency transfers (low FX margin). Local rails like SEPA/Pix are cheapest within regions.</div>

              <div class="q">Q: Can I use personal PayPal for my business?</div>
              <div>A: You can, but a business account gives better features (invoicing, higher limits, seller protections) and is recommended.</div>

              <div class="q">Q: How do I handle refunds and chargebacks?</div>
              <div>A: Keep policies clear, document deliveries, and use dispute resolution tools provided by your payment processor (PayPal/Stripe).</div>

              <div class="q">Q: What about tax & reporting?</div>
              <div>A: Track income by currency and region. Consult an accountant familiar with cross-border sales and VAT/GST rules in your markets.</div>
            </div>
          </section>
